.TH "LIGHTNING-NODE-PEER-FEATURES" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-node-peer-features \- show feature bits for a peer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning node-peer-features
.I peer_id
.SH DESCRIPTION
Returns the feature bits advertised by the specified peer along with connection status.
.PP
Output: JSON object with peer_id, features (hex string), connected (bool).
Returns
.B {"error":"peer_not_found"}
if the peer_id is not known.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Always.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lightning-peer-reputation (1),
.BR lightning-peer-info (1)
